column5: Wow, those look like some World Record Perch! What Lake? LMAO
arent these the guys from movie "meet dave" ?

In a NewYork city apartment a young boy named Josh Morrison (Austin Lynd Myers) watches through his telescope an approaching object coming from the sky. It is a golf ball-sized metal ball which flies through the window of his room and lands in his fishbowl, quickly draining the water. He keeps it and shows it at school in a science class presentation. Some months later, on Liberty Island a massive fireball crash lands. The fireball is actually a spaceship resembling a human (Eddie Murphy). It is controlled by 100 humanoid aliens, each one inch tall.
I've caught bigger perch than that... on a surface lure... 2lb test line.... in a "dead" lake.
That's an old trick, they have their arms outstretched toward the camera. I always check the size of the hands...dead give away.
I wonder if they're as tasty as their north American cousins... Imagine getting a mess of those on Simcoe!!
imagine the size hole you'd need to drill...
